00:14:18,882 --> 00:14:20,848
♪ ♪

268
00:14:23,636 --> 00:14:25,187
Hello, James.

269
00:14:25,212 --> 00:14:27,212
It's been a while.

270
00:14:27,248 --> 00:14:30,240
Barbara, can you give us a moment?

271
00:14:30,718 --> 00:14:32,317
Sure.

272
00:14:32,353 --> 00:14:34,353
Have fun, lovebirds.

273
00:14:40,048 --> 00:14:42,027
What is your business with Barbara Kean?

274
00:14:42,103 --> 00:14:44,871
You're worried that I told her
about our arrangement?

275
00:14:44,906 --> 00:14:46,539
(SCOFFS)

276
00:14:46,574 --> 00:14:48,447
I know how to keep a secret.

277
00:14:48,478 --> 00:14:50,510
Now, I want my man Carmichael released

278
00:14:50,545 --> 00:14:53,446
- from GCPD custody.
- That wasn't the deal.

279
00:14:53,481 --> 00:14:56,471
GORDON: You run the underworld.
I run the GCPD.

280
00:14:56,502 --> 00:14:58,699
Your guy got arrested.
That's on him.

281
00:14:58,785 --> 00:15:01,220
Let me make something clear.

282
00:15:01,472 --> 00:15:04,653
Our deal is whatever I say it is.

283
00:15:04,708 --> 00:15:06,575
Unless you want people to know

284
00:15:06,637 --> 00:15:08,728
you're responsible
for bringing the Pyg to town.

285
00:15:09,779 --> 00:15:12,533
You brought him to Gotham.
I was just trying to stop Penguin.

286
00:15:12,588 --> 00:15:15,986
But you covered it up and
took credit for killing him.

287
00:15:16,049 --> 00:15:17,723
Word gets out, you're destroyed.

288
00:15:17,759 --> 00:15:20,860
Along with your beloved GCPD.

289
00:15:20,964 --> 00:15:25,633
And if I go down... so will you.

290
00:15:25,721 --> 00:15:28,433
And I think you like being
queen of the underworld.

291
00:15:28,505 --> 00:15:32,107
You still think you know
what I will and won't do.

292
00:15:32,142 --> 00:15:33,942
I know a bluff when I see one.

293
00:15:37,681 --> 00:15:39,280
I have a job to do.

294
00:15:42,452 --> 00:15:44,233
Selina!

295
00:15:44,354 --> 00:15:47,288
Oh, hey, Jim. I found Selina.
She went that way.

296
00:15:47,324 --> 00:15:50,225
(INMATES SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

297
00:15:51,995 --> 00:15:53,261
(SHOUTING)

298
00:15:53,296 --> 00:15:55,263
No, no, no!

299
00:15:55,298 --> 00:15:57,188
INMATE: Shut your beak.

300
00:15:57,376 --> 00:16:00,510
- OSWALD: No! No. No. No...
- (INMATES LAUGHING)

301
00:16:00,570 --> 00:16:01,703
(SHOUTS)

302
00:16:09,050 --> 00:16:12,680
- What do you want?
- I told you, Pengy.

303
00:16:12,716 --> 00:16:15,717
I'm gonna cure you
of this sad sack mopey act.

304
00:16:15,752 --> 00:16:17,619
And the best cure

305
00:16:17,654 --> 00:16:20,418
is the laughing cure.

306
00:16:20,443 --> 00:16:22,376
(ALL LAUGH)

307
00:16:23,193 --> 00:16:24,659
Make me laugh.

308
00:16:24,988 --> 00:16:27,162
ALL (CHANTING):
Make him laugh! Make him laugh!

309
00:16:27,197 --> 00:16:29,831
So, what'll you be performing?

310
00:16:29,866 --> 00:16:32,000
Uh, contortionism?

311
00:16:32,035 --> 00:16:33,835
Juggling act? A tight five?

312
00:16:33,870 --> 00:16:36,304
Oh, what's that?

313
00:16:37,197 --> 00:16:39,698
You want to do a clown dance?

314
00:16:39,885 --> 00:16:41,885
- MAN: Yeah!
- Wonderful.

315
00:16:44,548 --> 00:16:46,214
I will not!

316
00:16:47,217 --> 00:16:49,017
- Huh?
- OSWALD: No.

317
00:16:50,053 --> 00:16:52,353
Hands off... No!

318
00:16:52,389 --> 00:16:54,088
- (OSWALD SHOUTS)
- ALL: Make him laugh!

319
00:16:54,124 --> 00:16:55,323
Make him laugh!

320
00:16:55,358 --> 00:16:58,059
Make him laugh! Make him laugh!

321
00:16:58,094 --> 00:17:00,495
- Make him laugh!
- (SHOES SQUEAKING)

322
00:17:00,530 --> 00:17:02,230
- Ugh...
- In your own time.

323
00:17:02,265 --> 00:17:03,832
(EXHALES)

324
00:17:05,869 --> 00:17:08,582
You have no idea how I've suffered.

325
00:17:08,707 --> 00:17:12,774
The betrayals I've endured.
Just... just leave me alone.

326
00:17:14,110 --> 00:17:15,910
- (CRYING): Leave me alone.
- Cut!

327
00:17:20,317 --> 00:17:21,716
Hey.

328
00:17:22,252 --> 00:17:24,807
Oswald, Oswald, Oswald.

329
00:17:24,862 --> 00:17:28,089
You are trapped in a prison.

330
00:17:28,124 --> 00:17:30,358
In here.

331
00:17:30,596 --> 00:17:33,385
- And I'm offering you the key.
- (GROANS)

332
00:17:33,430 --> 00:17:35,930
So... dance.

333
00:17:35,966 --> 00:17:39,934
(SHOUTS) Make him laugh! Make him laugh!
Make him laugh!

334
00:17:39,970 --> 00:17:42,303
- Now we're talking.
- (SHOES SQUEAKING)

335
00:17:42,339 --> 00:17:43,872
I can feel the funny coming.

336
00:17:43,907 --> 00:17:45,073
Here it comes!

337
00:17:45,108 --> 00:17:47,609
Here comes the funny. Okay.

338
00:17:47,644 --> 00:17:48,710
(YELLING)

339
00:17:48,745 --> 00:17:49,978
(SHOES SQUEAKING)

340
00:17:51,114 --> 00:17:52,580
(INMATES GASPING)

341
00:17:52,616 --> 00:17:54,115
WOMAN: And you're down.

342
00:17:57,587 --> 00:17:59,387
Fred Astaire you are not.

343
00:18:01,491 --> 00:18:05,326
- We'll try again tomorrow.
- MAN: Come on!

344
00:18:05,362 --> 00:18:06,961
(ALL CHEERING)

345
00:18:22,712 --> 00:18:25,179
Ow! What the hell, man?

346
00:18:25,225 --> 00:18:26,695
Why were you running, Selina?

347
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,523
'Cause a jerk with a badge
was chasing me.

348
00:18:28,552 --> 00:18:30,318
So not because you were
in Roland Charles's house

349
00:18:30,353 --> 00:18:32,287
last night when he was
turned into a tree?

350
00:18:32,485 --> 00:18:34,685
His family saw a redhead and a brunette.

351
00:18:34,753 --> 00:18:37,064
The brunette was carrying a
leather whip just like yours.

352
00:18:37,089 --> 00:18:38,555
Tell me I'm crazy.

353
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:41,496
I swear, I was only there
to rob the place.

354
00:18:41,531 --> 00:18:43,164
So what about the redhead?

355
00:18:43,199 --> 00:18:45,433
She killed some tweaker in
the Narrows the same way.

356
00:18:45,468 --> 00:18:47,101
I need a name.

357
00:18:47,137 --> 00:18:48,970
Ivy Pepper.

358
00:18:49,005 --> 00:18:51,139
Try again. I know Ivy.

359
00:18:51,174 --> 00:18:52,707
No, Gordon, she's changed.

360
00:18:52,736 --> 00:18:54,469
Like, a lot.

361
00:18:54,494 --> 00:18:57,045
She can use plants
to hypnotize people, and poison them.

362
00:18:57,830 --> 00:18:59,314
So why'd she want to kill Roland?

363
00:18:59,349 --> 00:19:01,049
'Cause he works for Wayne Enterprises.

364
00:19:01,084 --> 00:19:03,544
- Wayne Enterprises.
- She's obsessed with this

365
00:19:03,569 --> 00:19:05,349
super secret project they're doing.

366
00:19:06,201 --> 00:19:09,948
Lucius lied. Come on. Let's go.

367
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:18,332
Admiring my handiwork?

368
00:19:18,903 --> 00:19:20,636
Excuse me?

369
00:19:23,054 --> 00:19:25,154
Look how beautiful he became.

370
00:19:27,410 --> 00:19:29,651
And all it took...

371
00:19:29,879 --> 00:19:32,714
was a little scratch.

372
00:19:33,183 --> 00:19:35,011
Oh...

373
00:19:35,352 --> 00:19:37,722
Well, what do you want from me?

374
00:19:37,769 --> 00:19:39,721
I want to know about Project M.

375
00:19:40,917 --> 00:19:42,991
- What is Project M?
- Mm-mm-mm.

376
00:19:43,026 --> 00:19:44,926
Bruce Wayne told me everything.

377
00:19:45,199 --> 00:19:47,428
How he didn't even trust himself
with the location,

378
00:19:47,464 --> 00:19:49,230
but that you know where it is.

379
00:19:51,301 --> 00:19:54,102
And you're going to take me to it.

380
00:19:57,874 --> 00:19:59,994
But first,

381
00:20:00,572 --> 00:20:02,932
you probably want to tell me
I'm beautiful.

382
00:20:02,971 --> 00:20:04,112
Yeah.

383
00:20:04,267 --> 00:20:05,943
Yes.

384
00:20:09,587 --> 00:20:11,120
(CRACKLING)

385
00:20:12,902 --> 00:20:14,575
BRUCE: Help!

386
00:20:15,493 --> 00:20:18,094
Help! Somebody help me!

387
00:20:22,303 --> 00:20:23,835
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

388
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:35,560
(BARBARA LAUGHING)

389
00:20:35,683 --> 00:20:38,183
Jim. Jim, you need to help me.

390
00:20:38,223 --> 00:20:39,683
GORDON: Ouch.

391
00:20:39,723 --> 00:20:41,890
Looks like you cut yourself
shaving, old man.

392
00:20:41,925 --> 00:20:43,825
Jim, it's me, it's Bruce.

393
00:20:43,861 --> 00:20:45,727
I'm Bruce Wayne.

394
00:20:45,762 --> 00:20:47,129
(BOTH LAUGH)

395
00:20:47,164 --> 00:20:50,365
BARBARA: Honey, I think we'd know
if you were Bruce Wayne.

396
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:51,867
He's the one throwing this shindig.

397
00:20:51,902 --> 00:20:54,569
That's him yonder.

398
00:20:54,605 --> 00:20:56,872
THOMPKINS (LAUGHING):
Bruce, you're incorrigible.

399
00:20:56,907 --> 00:20:58,874
- I may bust a gut.
- (LAUGHS)

400
00:20:58,909 --> 00:21:01,292
Luckily, I am a doctor.

401
00:21:01,512 --> 00:21:05,046
(LAUGHS): Ain't he the cat's pajamas?

402
00:21:05,472 --> 00:21:06,980
Come on.

403
00:21:10,387 --> 00:21:12,152
Easy there, sport.

404
00:21:12,190 --> 00:21:14,423
- That's Italian velvet.
- What did you do?

405
00:21:14,462 --> 00:21:16,330
Where's Ra's al Ghul?

406
00:21:16,392 --> 00:21:17,921
Ra's al who?

407
00:21:17,957 --> 00:21:19,951
That's my face. He gave you my face.

408
00:21:20,006 --> 00:21:21,091
That's my face!

409
00:21:21,126 --> 00:21:23,093
Think you've been
hitting the gin. (CHUCKLES)

410
00:21:23,128 --> 00:21:26,564
Give me back my face! I'm Bruce Wayne!

411
00:21:26,839 --> 00:21:30,362
Get off of me. You're ruining my fun.

412
00:21:32,542 --> 00:21:35,072
(COCKNEY ACCENT): Everything
all right, Master Bruce?

413
00:21:35,107 --> 00:21:36,907
- (CHICKEN CLUCKS)
- Yes, thank you.

414
00:21:36,942 --> 00:21:38,475
Just getting rid of the riffraff.

415
00:21:38,510 --> 00:21:40,477
(CHICKEN CLUCKS)

416
00:21:45,350 --> 00:21:46,717
Ha, ha!

417
00:21:47,631 --> 00:21:50,428
Dude, what is it with you
and the arm-grabbing?

418
00:21:50,467 --> 00:21:52,064
Harper. I need keys to lockup.

419
00:21:52,089 --> 00:21:53,320
- And is Lucius in his office?
- Let go.

420
00:21:53,355 --> 00:21:56,158
Lucius? No, he left with Ivy
a little while ago.

421
00:21:56,220 --> 00:21:57,424
Ivy Pepper?

422
00:21:57,459 --> 00:21:59,126
- She was here?
- Yeah.

423
00:21:59,161 --> 00:22:01,061
She asked me
to introduce her to everyone.

424
00:22:01,096 --> 00:22:02,729
Isn't she the coolest?

425
00:22:02,765 --> 00:22:04,131
She's a psycho

426
00:22:04,166 --> 00:22:06,089
who turned a guy into a potted plant.

427
00:22:06,159 --> 00:22:08,168
What's going on with you?

428
00:22:08,859 --> 00:22:11,128
Did he just say Ivy's a psycho?

429
00:22:11,542 --> 00:22:13,006
But Ivy's the best.

430
00:22:15,878 --> 00:22:18,720
Is this the, uh, hypnosis
I've been hearing about?

431
00:22:18,745 --> 00:22:20,380
I'm gonna say yeah.

432
00:22:20,416 --> 00:22:22,983
And until it fades,
they'll do anything for her.

433
00:22:23,175 --> 00:22:25,245
And think she's the coolest.

434
00:22:27,589 --> 00:22:30,019
What do you mean by "Ivy's a psycho"?

435
00:22:30,059 --> 00:22:32,526
Hold that thought, Harper.

436
00:22:32,562 --> 00:22:34,261
We'll be right back.

437
00:22:34,699 --> 00:22:37,323
You hear what the captain
said about Ivy?

438
00:22:37,348 --> 00:22:40,249
- But Ivy's awesome.
- Yeah, she is the coolest.

439
00:22:44,355 --> 00:22:46,422
(DOOR OPENS)

440
00:22:49,593 --> 00:22:50,693
(GASPS, SCREAMS)

441
00:22:50,728 --> 00:22:52,618
No more, no more!

442
00:22:52,763 --> 00:22:54,704
You have a visitor.

443
00:22:54,932 --> 00:22:56,498
(WHIMPERS)

444
00:23:02,106 --> 00:23:04,135
Hello, Oswald.

445
00:23:05,619 --> 00:23:07,509
I see Arkham's treating you well.

446
00:23:07,545 --> 00:23:09,745
(LAUGHS)

447
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:11,280
I take it you're here to gloat.

448
00:23:11,541 --> 00:23:13,215
You are correct.

449
00:23:14,251 --> 00:23:16,174
And why not?

450
00:23:16,454 --> 00:23:18,954
I am in an insane asylum.

451
00:23:18,989 --> 00:23:20,189
(NYGMA LAUGHS)

452
00:23:20,224 --> 00:23:22,758
Being pummeled by lunatics.

453
00:23:22,793 --> 00:23:24,193
(LAUGHS)

454
00:23:24,228 --> 00:23:27,529
Then again, at least I'm not a moron.

455
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:32,104
I may not be the man I once was.

456
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:35,128
But I have many things
that you do not have.

457
00:23:35,172 --> 00:23:37,239
A purpose.

458
00:23:37,264 --> 00:23:38,540
Friends.

459
00:23:38,576 --> 00:23:39,775
You have neither of those.

460
00:23:40,275 --> 00:23:42,311
And I wanted you to see that.

461
00:23:46,454 --> 00:23:48,290
No.

462
00:23:49,118 --> 00:23:50,451
I know you.

463
00:23:50,524 --> 00:23:52,907
There's something else going on.

464
00:23:53,052 --> 00:23:54,685
Something else brought you here.

465
00:23:56,994 --> 00:23:58,660
There's nothing else.

466
00:23:58,928 --> 00:24:01,330
I wanted you to see how well

467
00:24:01,365 --> 00:24:02,531
I am doing.

468
00:24:02,566 --> 00:24:04,600
And I wanted to see
how miserable you are.

469
00:24:04,635 --> 00:24:07,102
Mission accomplished. (LAUGHS)

470
00:24:07,138 --> 00:24:08,757
Ed.

471
00:24:09,540 --> 00:24:11,073
I'm gonna be out of here soon.

472
00:24:11,514 --> 00:24:13,475
And once I am,

473
00:24:13,511 --> 00:24:18,981
I am going to wipe that smile

474
00:24:19,016 --> 00:24:20,504
off of your face.

475
00:24:20,778 --> 00:24:22,378
Preferably with a chain saw.

476
00:24:22,453 --> 00:24:23,652
Ow.

477
00:24:23,687 --> 00:24:25,421
How are you gonna do that?

478
00:24:25,456 --> 00:24:27,523
You have no friends.

479
00:24:27,558 --> 00:24:29,740
No one to help you escape.

480
00:24:30,334 --> 00:24:32,662
You are utterly alone.

481
00:24:34,999 --> 00:24:36,832
Good-bye, Oswald.

482
00:24:38,569 --> 00:24:39,768
- (LOCK BUZZES)
- Sorry,

483
00:24:39,804 --> 00:24:42,271
but I don't put too much stock

484
00:24:42,306 --> 00:24:45,207
in the opinions of simpletons!

485
00:24:59,557 --> 00:25:01,457
"I am held captive all day.

486
00:25:01,597 --> 00:25:03,480
"My brilliance locked away.

487
00:25:03,594 --> 00:25:05,542
"This prison must be broken.

488
00:25:05,663 --> 00:25:07,441
"The key?

489
00:25:09,667 --> 00:25:11,567
My name, which must be spoken."

490
00:25:11,602 --> 00:25:14,470
(LAUGHS)

491
00:25:16,436 --> 00:25:18,669
You're still in there. (LAUGHS)

492
00:25:21,572 --> 00:25:23,710
That's why you came.

493
00:25:24,012 --> 00:25:26,380
You're still there. (LAUGHS)

494
00:25:26,517 --> 00:25:29,351
And you're gonna help me
find a way out of here.

495
00:25:29,386 --> 00:25:30,986
- Hello?
- (DRAWER CLOSES)

496
00:25:31,021 --> 00:25:32,287
We should be leaving.

497
00:25:32,322 --> 00:25:34,646
Not until we find out
where Ivy took Lucius.

498
00:25:34,679 --> 00:25:36,346
- There has to be something.
- (TAPE RECORDER WHIRS)

499
00:25:42,233 --> 00:25:44,199
(TAPE REWINDING)

500
00:25:45,402 --> 00:25:46,902
(BUTTON CLICKS)

501
00:25:46,937 --> 00:25:49,371
IVY: <i>You know where it is and
you are going to take me to it.</i>

502
00:25:49,398 --> 00:25:52,441
LUCIUS: <i>Mmm. You're so incredible.</i>

503
00:25:52,476 --> 00:25:53,742
IVY: <i>Uh-huh.</i>

504
00:25:53,777 --> 00:25:56,211
<i>Where is Project M?</i>

505
00:25:56,247 --> 00:25:58,113
LUCIUS: <i>Wayne Biotech
has a secret facility</i>

506
00:25:58,148 --> 00:26:00,499
<i>outside the city
at the edge of Kane Park.</i>

507
00:26:00,553 --> 00:26:02,787
- (BUTTON CLICKS)
- Good man, Lucius.

508
00:26:02,827 --> 00:26:04,593
OFFICER: In here.

509
00:26:05,389 --> 00:26:06,922
HARPER: Hey, Cap.

510
00:26:06,957 --> 00:26:08,587
The boys and I were talking.

511
00:26:08,619 --> 00:26:09,989
And we didn't really like the way

512
00:26:10,014 --> 00:26:11,556
that you were talking about Ivy.

513
00:26:11,595 --> 00:26:13,611
I told you we should have left.

514
00:26:14,298 --> 00:26:17,566
Look, I think you misinterpreted
what I was saying.

515
00:26:19,136 --> 00:26:20,702
You called Ivy a psycho.

516
00:26:21,105 --> 00:26:23,772
That's a term of endearment. (CHUCKLES)

517
00:26:23,807 --> 00:26:25,894
I love Ivy. I think she's great.

518
00:26:26,010 --> 00:26:27,543
What about you?

519
00:26:27,578 --> 00:26:28,744
Do you love Ivy?

520
00:26:28,779 --> 00:26:30,779
(LAUGHS) Yeah.

521
00:26:30,814 --> 00:26:32,614
I love Ivy.

522
00:26:33,582 --> 00:26:36,356
- How much?
- I love Ivy

523
00:26:36,426 --> 00:26:39,478
so much that I wish I could be her.

524
00:26:41,659 --> 00:26:43,091
You're not really selling it.

525
00:26:43,423 --> 00:26:44,927
And you think you did?

526
00:26:45,455 --> 00:26:47,062
Run.

527
00:26:47,097 --> 00:26:48,096
HARPER: Get 'em!

528
00:26:50,377 --> 00:26:51,767
